    <h3>Player versus Environment (PvE)</h3>
      <p>PvE in Destiny is very differnt from PvE in other games because it has so much content with some RPG mechanics. For example Call of Duty only has a single-player/co-op campaign and zombies mode. Battlefield, only has a single-player campaign. Now those compared to Destiny's strikes, raids, public events, quests, nightfall strikes, arena, and full story missions, are NOTHING. In Destiny you can also experience all those activities with your friends to make the game even more fun. Strikes are 3-player activities that send your fireteam on dangerous mission to take out an enemy of the Darkness from taking over a certain planet or area. Nightfalls are harder versions of strikes with more powerful enemies and completion rewards. Raids are 6-player activities that embark your fireteam on the biggest and hardest content of the game. Raids challenge you and your fireteam in boss fights where your team needs to figure out and create a strategy to defeat each boss as you advance through mazes and encounters. Arena is a 3-player form of survival called The Prison of Elders(easy) or Challenge of the Elders(hard) with boss fights and objectives. Public Events are random activities that anyone can join as you patrol on planets. Finally quests are a series of steps you have to complete in a certain activity to earn loot. As you participate in any of these activities you able to rank up your faction for rewards as well recieve the activity based loot you earn from any PvE event.</p>
    <img src="http://www.gifmania.com.es/Videojuegos/Videojuegos-Disparos/Destiny/Hechicero-Colmenas-87760.gif" width=550>
