    <h3>Player versus Player (PvP)</h3>
      <p>Just like many other games Destiny has its own competitive mode called The Crucible. Destiny's Crucible can hold matches of 4, 6, or 12 maximum players. The match lobbies are split into the two teams Alpha and Bravo. The Crucible features the many modes but the basic ones are Clash, Control, Rift, Skirmish, Salvage, Elimination, and Rumble. Clash is another name for the classic 6v6 team deathmatch game mode that appears in most FPS games. Control is a 6v6 objective based game mode where two teams have to capture zones A, B, and C. Rift is another 6v6 objective game mode where you have to take a spark in the center of the map and score it into the enemy rift. Skirmish and Salvage are both 3v3 modes where you can revive fallen teammates but Skirmish is team deathmatch and Salvage is an objective mode of salavaging lost relics that appear within the map. Rumble is free-for-all where you're on your own with no one watching your back from enemy fire. Elimination is the most intense PvP mode in Destiny like Skirmish but you have to eliminate the enemy team with you and your team having only ONE life without respawns unless you are revived. At the 1 minute mark, if no team has been eliminated your team has to capture a zone in an area of the map to claim victory of 1 round. To win an Elimination match you have to win 5 rounds. Just like PvE The Crucible can be played with your own fireteam. Soon for Rise of Iron expansion Bungie will be adding the mode Supremacy and private matches to Destiny.</p>
